IT STILL SEEMS LIKE MY SON IS ALIVE

15
00:04:25,398 --> 00:04:27,633
- Ms. YANG Mija
- Here

16
00:04:27,634 --> 00:04:30,634
This way

17
00:04:44,484 --> 00:04:46,652
What's wrong?

18
00:04:46,653 --> 00:04:48,920
My arm

19
00:04:48,921 --> 00:04:51,921
My right arm feels prickly

20
00:04:58,097 --> 00:04:59,598
Does it hurt here?

21
00:04:59,599 --> 00:05:02,599
No, it doesn't hurt,
itjust feels prickly

22
00:05:02,802 --> 00:05:05,671
Like...

23
00:05:05,672 --> 00:05:08,307
That thing is passing through

24
00:05:08,308 --> 00:05:11,243
What's it called?

25
00:05:11,244 --> 00:05:14,244
It's been like this lately

26
00:05:15,481 --> 00:05:18,481
It's... like energy

27
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:23,720
- Electricity?
- Right, electricity!

28
00:05:23,790 --> 00:05:26,790
It's like electricity's
passing through

29
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:30,160
I'm forgetting words lately

30
00:05:31,064 --> 00:05:34,064
Yesterday, I couldn't
remember,'bleach'

31
00:05:36,469 --> 00:05:39,469
I could only remember, 'Clorox. '

32
00:05:39,806 --> 00:05:42,806
We used to call bleach, 'Clorox'
back in the old days

33
00:05:43,109 --> 00:05:45,577
How long have you
been like this?

34
00:05:45,578 --> 00:05:48,578
For the past couple ofdays

35
00:05:49,615 --> 00:05:52,615
No, your forgetfulness
When did it start?

36
00:05:53,353 --> 00:05:54,886
When did it start?

37
00:05:54,887 --> 00:05:57,887
Maybe this summer or spring?

38
00:05:59,992 --> 00:06:02,992
How old are you, ma'am?

39
00:06:03,029 --> 00:06:06,029
Sixty five, no, sixty six

40
00:06:10,536 --> 00:06:13,536
Your arm's prickly because
the muscles are in knots

41
00:06:15,274 --> 00:06:17,642
Start some light exercising

42
00:06:17,643 --> 00:06:20,643
I'm more concerned that you
can't remember words

43
00:06:24,250 --> 00:06:27,250
It could be a bad sign

44
00:06:27,387 --> 00:06:30,387
I recommend you get an
overhaul at a big hospital

45
00:06:32,458 --> 00:06:34,626
A big hospital?

46
00:06:34,627 --> 00:06:37,627
Yes, like a big general hospital
in Seoul

47
00:06:39,332 --> 00:06:42,332
I'll write a reference for you

48
00:06:44,871 --> 00:06:47,871
I'm at the hospital

49
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:50,375
My arm feels prickly

50
00:06:50,376 --> 00:06:53,376
It's continues feeling prickly

51
00:06:53,946 --> 00:06:56,946
I kept telling myselfto see
a doctor and I finally did

52
00:06:58,518 --> 00:07:01,518
Who else would come
with me, you idiot?

53
00:07:05,725 --> 00:07:08,725
Your mom's okay

54
00:07:10,096 --> 00:07:13,096
Others my age usually suffer
from neuralgia or arthritis

55
00:07:17,336 --> 00:07:20,336
I'm okay

56
00:07:22,108 --> 00:07:25,108
Don't cry, mom...

57
00:07:25,278 --> 00:07:28,278
How could you be so cruel!

58
00:07:28,848 --> 00:07:31,349
How could you...

59
00:07:31,350 --> 00:07:33,852
You can't go way like this!

60
00:07:33,853 --> 00:07:36,853
Where are you! Where did she go!

61
00:07:38,591 --> 00:07:41,591
Oh god!

62
00:07:46,666 --> 00:07:49,666
You cruel wench!

63
00:07:51,070 --> 00:07:54,070
Where is she?
Where!

64
00:07:57,109 --> 00:08:00,109
Mom...

65
00:08:29,976 --> 00:08:32,143
- Hello
- You're here

66
00:08:32,144 --> 00:08:34,746
You're a little late

67
00:08:34,747 --> 00:08:36,548
I went to the hospital

68
00:08:36,549 --> 00:08:39,549
He called twiceI received two calls, asking
whyyou weren't coming

69
00:08:49,262 --> 00:08:52,262
Dad, the maid's on her way up

70
00:09:12,318 --> 00:09:14,920
This one, this one

71
00:09:14,921 --> 00:09:17,921
Sit still! I told you
to sit still!

72
00:09:19,125 --> 00:09:20,325
Stop it!

73
00:09:20,326 --> 00:09:23,326
How will I undress you
ifyou resist like this?

74
00:09:23,963 --> 00:09:26,963
Right, that's it
Pull this leg out

75
00:09:28,601 --> 00:09:31,601
That's howyou do it

76
00:09:43,149 --> 00:09:46,149
Is it hot? It's okay, isn't it?

77
00:09:46,252 --> 00:09:49,252
Sit still!

78
00:09:49,255 --> 00:09:51,957
Sit still, I say! Stop it!

79
00:09:51,958 --> 00:09:54,292
- Why are you shouting?
- What?

80
00:09:54,293 --> 00:09:55,360
What's that?

81
00:09:55,361 --> 00:09:58,361
My hearing... so why...?

82
00:10:00,900 --> 00:10:03,900
Your hearing is fine so
why I am shouting?

83
00:10:05,104 --> 00:10:07,572
I'm sorry

84
00:10:07,573 --> 00:10:10,573
I won't shout again

85
00:10:25,124 --> 00:10:27,726
Sir, I'll be leaving

86
00:10:27,727 --> 00:10:29,561
Goodbye

87
00:10:29,562 --> 00:10:32,197
- Done?
- Pardon?

88
00:10:32,198 --> 00:10:35,198
- I said, are you done?
- Yes, I'm done

89
00:10:37,236 --> 00:10:40,236
- Already?
- What do you mean?

90
00:10:40,239 --> 00:10:42,607
It's already been 3 hours

91
00:10:42,608 --> 00:10:45,608
I did the laundry, the cleaning
and all my chores

92
00:11:01,127 --> 00:11:04,127
Good

93
00:11:05,364 --> 00:11:07,799
Thankyou, sir

94
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:10,001
Don't...

95
00:11:10,002 --> 00:11:12,704
tell anyone...

96
00:11:12,705 --> 00:11:15,705
I gave it to you

97
00:11:16,876 --> 00:11:19,876
Okay

98
00:11:27,019 --> 00:11:30,019
How generous!

99
00:11:38,364 --> 00:11:41,364
Thankyou

100
00:11:41,767 --> 00:11:44,736
Did he yell at you today?

101
00:11:44,737 --> 00:11:46,871
Ofcourse he did

102
00:11:46,872 --> 00:11:49,872
I doesn't matter cause
I yelled back at him

103
00:11:50,443 --> 00:11:52,644
Here

104
00:11:52,645 --> 00:11:55,645
- He gave me 10,000Won
- He did?

105
00:11:57,316 --> 00:12:00,316
But he told me not to tell anyone

106
00:12:01,921 --> 00:12:03,855
When it's only 10,000Won

107
00:12:03,856 --> 00:12:06,856
My father-in-law is
notorious for being stingy

108
00:12:07,460 --> 00:12:10,460
He must really like you. To give
you an amount like that

109
00:12:11,864 --> 00:12:14,864
Anyway, do you always look
so chic like that?

110
00:12:15,501 --> 00:12:18,501
Do I look chic?
I'm not chic at all

111
00:12:20,506 --> 00:12:23,174
Where is it? Not again

112
00:12:23,175 --> 00:12:25,343
What are you looking for?

113
00:12:25,344 --> 00:12:28,344
What's that thing?
I can't remember the word

114
00:12:30,316 --> 00:12:32,383
What you put money in

115
00:12:32,384 --> 00:12:33,885
It's this big

116
00:12:33,886 --> 00:12:35,854
A wallet?

117
00:12:35,855 --> 00:12:37,822
That's it, a wallet!

118
00:12:37,823 --> 00:12:40,792
Where's my wallet?

119
00:12:40,793 --> 00:12:43,793
What's this?

120
00:12:46,799 --> 00:12:49,799
I'm so out of it these days

121
00:12:54,907 --> 00:12:57,907
At the hospital
I saw something...

122
00:12:58,344 --> 00:13:01,344
A local middle school girl's
body was found in the river

123
00:13:03,082 --> 00:13:06,082
And brought to the hospital

124
00:13:06,685 --> 00:13:09,685
They said it was suicide
byjumping offthe bridge

125
00:13:11,957 --> 00:13:14,957
The poor girl's mom was
totally out of her mind...

126
00:13:20,866 --> 00:13:23,866
- I'll be on my way.
- See you the day after tomorrow

127
00:13:50,095 --> 00:13:53,095
The deadline's over

128
00:13:59,171 --> 00:14:02,171
What're you drying?

129
00:14:03,142 --> 00:14:06,142
Did your daughter call?

130
00:14:11,250 --> 00:14:14,250
LITERARY CLASS FORTHE PUBLIC
YOU CAN ALSO BE A POET!

131
00:14:23,429 --> 00:14:26,429
Are you home, Wook?

132
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:30,600
Why's the music on so loud?

133
00:14:31,704 --> 00:14:34,704
You'll bring down the house

134
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:42,947
What's wrong?

135
00:14:42,948 --> 00:14:45,483
Are you feeling sick?

136
00:14:45,484 --> 00:14:48,484
Don't bother

137
00:15:25,658 --> 00:15:28,658
I called you during the day
but you weren't answering

138
00:15:29,962 --> 00:15:31,562
I never got your call

139
00:15:31,563 --> 00:15:34,563
How can you say that
when I called twice

140
00:15:34,667 --> 00:15:37,101
I'm not lying

141
00:15:37,102 --> 00:15:40,102
It's cause my mobile's junk
Buy me a new one

142
00:15:40,773 --> 00:15:42,373
I'm annoyed with my mobile

143
00:15:42,374 --> 00:15:45,143
You just bought it, so why
do you need a new one?

144
00:15:45,144 --> 00:15:48,144
- But I had it for 1 and 1/2 yr
- No you didn't

145
00:15:49,682 --> 00:15:52,682
I got it during the 1 st semester
of my 2nd year

146
00:15:54,453 --> 00:15:57,453
Which only shows how
carelesslyyou've used it

147
00:15:59,792 --> 00:16:02,792
You're sprouting a moustache,
but acting like a child

148
00:16:06,565 --> 00:16:08,800
Why'd you call anyway?

149
00:16:08,801 --> 00:16:11,801
I heard a girl in your school
killed herself...

150
00:16:12,638 --> 00:16:15,173
byjumping into the river

151
00:16:15,174 --> 00:16:17,842
I wanted to askyou about it

152
00:16:17,843 --> 00:16:19,410
Ask me what?

153
00:16:19,411 --> 00:16:22,411
Who she was, why'd she
kill herselfthat young

154
00:16:25,951 --> 00:16:28,553
I don't know her that well

155
00:16:28,554 --> 00:16:30,288
What's her name?

156
00:16:30,289 --> 00:16:32,457
Why do you need her name?

157
00:16:32,458 --> 00:16:34,926
Aren't you in the same grade?

158
00:16:34,927 --> 00:16:37,927
I don't know everyone
in the same grade

159
00:16:43,268 --> 00:16:46,268
Grandma can't afford a new
mobile. Askyour mom for one

160
00:16:48,807 --> 00:16:51,807
What? That's not fair!

161
00:17:21,407 --> 00:17:24,407
Hey! Play with a bit
more spirit

162
00:17:24,977 --> 00:17:27,045
This is no fun

163
00:17:27,046 --> 00:17:29,447
Just try

164
00:17:29,448 --> 00:17:32,448
The doctor told me to exercise

165
00:17:47,466 --> 00:17:50,466
What are you doing?

166
00:17:53,372 --> 00:17:55,373
Where are you going?

167
00:17:55,374 --> 00:17:57,175
Gotta go see my buddies

168
00:17:57,176 --> 00:18:00,176
You shouldn't go out
at this hour!

169
00:18:08,754 --> 00:18:11,754
The electricity bill's
quite high this month

170
00:18:11,990 --> 00:18:14,759
Wook's always on the computer...

171
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:16,594
playing music all the time

172
00:18:16,595 --> 00:18:19,595
He even sleeps with the music on

173
00:18:19,898 --> 00:18:22,867
How am I supposed to scold him?

174
00:18:22,868 --> 00:18:24,735
Well what can I say?

175
00:18:24,736 --> 00:18:27,736
He's the master ofthe house

176
00:18:28,774 --> 00:18:30,141
What?

177
00:18:30,142 --> 00:18:33,142
The Cultural Center

178
00:18:34,012 --> 00:18:36,581
To learn poetry

179
00:18:36,582 --> 00:18:39,183
What? Right

180
00:18:39,184 --> 00:18:41,619
I do have a poet's vein

181
00:18:41,620 --> 00:18:44,620
Right. I do like flowers
and say odd things

182
00:19:13,118 --> 00:19:15,620
I'm here for the literary class

183
00:19:15,621 --> 00:19:18,621
Literary class?
But it's all closed

184
00:19:19,091 --> 00:19:22,091
I know...

185
00:19:22,194 --> 00:19:25,194
But can't you accept
one more person?

186
00:19:26,131 --> 00:19:28,499
I don't know...

187
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:31,500
I really want to take this class

188
00:19:32,137 --> 00:19:35,137
How should we deal with this?

189
00:19:39,645 --> 00:19:42,213
To write poetry, you must
see WELL

190
00:19:42,214 --> 00:19:45,214
The most important thing
in life is seeing

191
00:19:48,053 --> 00:19:50,021
SEE
See. It's to see

192
00:19:50,022 --> 00:19:52,023
- We live seeing things
- Right

193
00:19:52,024 --> 00:19:55,024
It's important to see everything
surrounding us well

194
00:19:55,027 --> 00:19:58,027
Now, I've brought
something with me

195
00:19:58,730 --> 00:19:59,730
What is it?

196
00:19:59,731 --> 00:20:02,200
- An apple
- Yes, it's an apple

197
00:20:02,201 --> 00:20:04,902
I went out of my way to bring it

198
00:20:04,903 --> 00:20:07,471
I'm a well-prepared teacher

199
00:20:07,472 --> 00:20:10,472
Others are not as well-prepared
as I am

200
00:20:20,519 --> 00:20:23,487
Now, about this apple

201
00:20:23,488 --> 00:20:26,488
How many times have you
seen an apple?

202
00:20:27,492 --> 00:20:29,694
A thousand?

203
00:20:29,695 --> 00:20:31,295
Ten thousand?

204
00:20:31,296 --> 00:20:33,331
A million? Wrong

205
00:20:33,332 --> 00:20:36,332
You've never seen
an apple before

206
00:20:37,102 --> 00:20:38,402
Not even once

207
00:20:38,403 --> 00:20:41,403
Up till now, you haven't
seen an apple for real

208
00:20:42,541 --> 00:20:45,142
To really know what an apple is...

209
00:20:45,143 --> 00:20:48,143
to be interested in it,
to understand it,

210
00:20:48,680 --> 00:20:51,680
to converse with it
is really seeing it

211
00:20:51,683 --> 00:20:54,683
Gazing at it for a while
and observing its shadow...

212
00:20:56,388 --> 00:20:59,388
feeling its every curve,
turning it around,

213
00:21:00,292 --> 00:21:02,860
taking a bite out of it,

214
00:21:02,861 --> 00:21:05,861
imagining the sunlight
absorbed in it...

215
00:21:06,465 --> 00:21:08,766
That is really seeing it

216
00:21:08,767 --> 00:21:11,767
Ifyou really see something,
you can feel...

217
00:21:13,572 --> 00:21:15,473
something naturally,

218
00:21:15,474 --> 00:21:17,875
like water gathering in a spring

219
00:21:17,876 --> 00:21:20,278
You should prepare
paper and a pencil,

220
00:21:20,279 --> 00:21:22,980
and wait for the moment to come

221
00:21:22,981 --> 00:21:25,383
Empty white paper...

222
00:21:25,384 --> 00:21:28,384
A world of pure potential,
a world before creation...

223
00:21:29,721 --> 00:21:32,556
This is the perfect
moment for a poet

224
00:21:32,557 --> 00:21:35,557
Hold your pencil over
that pure paper...

225
00:21:36,762 --> 00:21:39,163
I love pencils

226
00:21:39,164 --> 00:21:42,164
When I place a well-sharpened
pencil over a piece of paper,

227
00:21:43,302 --> 00:21:46,302
I feel full

228
00:21:46,705 --> 00:21:49,705
My heart flutters with the hope
ofwriting a good poem

229
00:21:51,777 --> 00:21:54,078
I love sharpening pencils

230
00:21:54,079 --> 00:21:55,713
The very fun ofa pencil
is hand-sharpening it

231
00:21:55,714 --> 00:21:57,281
I used to be good at
sharpening pencils

232
00:21:57,282 --> 00:21:59,116
Pardon?

233
00:21:59,117 --> 00:22:02,117
I was told to be a
good pencil-sharpener

234
00:22:03,155 --> 00:22:06,155
I sharpened all my brothers'
and sisters' pencils

235
00:22:07,392 --> 00:22:10,094
Is that so? Then, ma'am

236
00:22:10,095 --> 00:22:13,095
Why don't you sharpen
my pencil some day

237
00:22:13,732 --> 00:22:16,732
By the time this 1 month
class ends,

238
00:22:17,969 --> 00:22:20,969
I want you all to have written
a poem, okay?

239
00:22:21,773 --> 00:22:24,008
Everyone has to write one poem

240
00:22:24,009 --> 00:22:25,776
You need to write
to really know

241
00:22:25,777 --> 00:22:27,311
You'll never know if
you don't write

242
00:22:27,312 --> 00:22:30,312
So you have to write yourself

243
00:22:30,482 --> 00:22:33,482
Who has written a poem
at least once before?

244
00:22:36,688 --> 00:22:39,688
And who hasn't?

245
00:22:43,362 --> 00:22:44,962
Okay

246
00:22:44,963 --> 00:22:47,963
Nowyou will be writing
your own poem...

247
00:22:48,033 --> 00:22:50,101
for the first time in your life

248
00:22:50,102 --> 00:22:53,102
- Okay?
- Okay

249
00:23:46,958 --> 00:23:48,793
Who is it?

250
00:23:48,794 --> 00:23:49,960
My friends

251
00:23:49,961 --> 00:23:52,830
Why are your friends
here? It's late

252
00:23:52,831 --> 00:23:54,064
We need to talk

253
00:23:54,065 --> 00:23:57,065
About what? Haven't you seen
enough ofeach other?

254
00:24:00,071 --> 00:24:01,505
Hello, ma'am

255
00:24:01,506 --> 00:24:04,506
Good evening

256
00:24:25,730 --> 00:24:28,730
Why's the door locked?

257
00:24:30,268 --> 00:24:31,101
What?

258
00:24:31,102 --> 00:24:34,102
Why did you lock the door?

259
00:24:34,239 --> 00:24:37,239
Aren't you boys hungry?
Want some apples?

260
00:24:37,976 --> 00:24:40,976
No, stop bothering us
It's annoying

261
00:24:52,324 --> 00:24:55,324
Apples are better for eating
than looking at

262
00:25:30,228 --> 00:25:32,329
What are you looking at?

263
00:25:32,330 --> 00:25:35,330
The tree

264
00:25:35,734 --> 00:25:37,568
Why are you looking up the tree?

265
00:25:37,569 --> 00:25:39,970
To see it well

266
00:25:39,971 --> 00:25:42,907
To feel it,

267
00:25:42,908 --> 00:25:45,075
to understand its thoughts and...

268
00:25:45,076 --> 00:25:48,076
listen to what it says to me

269
00:26:00,592 --> 00:26:03,527
Hello?

270
00:26:03,528 --> 00:26:05,696
