02:10:11,203 --> 02:10:12,670
you've brought me flowers

1324
02:10:12,671 --> 02:10:14,372
Thankyou

1325
02:10:14,373 --> 02:10:17,373
I'm touched

1326
02:10:17,810 --> 02:10:19,644
Actually

1327
02:10:19,645 --> 02:10:22,079
We didn't bring it

1328
02:10:22,080 --> 02:10:24,582
Ms. YANG Mija placed it
there and left

1329
02:10:24,583 --> 02:10:27,583
Ms. YANG Mija?

1330
02:10:27,686 --> 02:10:30,521
She's even written a poem

1331
02:10:30,522 --> 02:10:33,522
But where has she gone?

1332
02:10:35,294 --> 02:10:38,294
Did anyone else bring a poem?

1333
02:10:38,864 --> 02:10:41,864
You were supposed to write
one poem by today

1334
02:10:42,434 --> 02:10:45,434
Anyone with a poem?

1335
02:10:46,371 --> 02:10:49,307
No one?

1336
02:10:49,308 --> 02:10:52,308
So the only one who has
written a poem is Ms. YANG

1337
02:10:54,446 --> 02:10:56,447
It's too difficult

1338
02:10:56,448 --> 02:10:57,782
No it's not

1339
02:10:57,783 --> 02:11:00,051
It's not difficult to write
a poem, but

1340
02:11:00,052 --> 02:11:03,052
to have the heart to write one

1341
02:11:03,388 --> 02:11:05,056
The heart to write a poem

1342
02:11:05,057 --> 02:11:06,524
Anyway,

1343
02:11:06,525 --> 02:11:08,860
Ms. YANG is not here, but

1344
02:11:08,861 --> 02:11:11,861
let's see what kind of poem
she has written

1345
02:11:12,664 --> 02:11:15,664
I'll read it on her behalf

1346
02:11:15,667 --> 02:11:18,636
The title is, 'Agnes' Song'

1347
02:11:18,637 --> 02:11:21,637
'Agnes' Song' byYANG Mija

1348
02:11:39,324 --> 02:11:42,324
Mom...

1349
02:12:24,469 --> 02:12:27,469
How is it over there?

1350
02:12:28,173 --> 02:12:31,173
How lonely is it?

1351
02:12:33,178 --> 02:12:36,178
Is it still glowing red at sunset?

1352
02:12:37,382 --> 02:12:40,382
Are the birds still singing on
the way to the forest?

1353
02:12:44,856 --> 02:12:47,856
Can you receive
the letter I dared not send?

1354
02:12:53,098 --> 02:12:55,733
Can I convey...

1355
02:12:55,734 --> 02:12:58,734
the confession I dared notmake?

1356
02:12:59,037 --> 02:13:02,037
Will time pass and roses fade?

1357
02:13:04,943 --> 02:13:07,943
Now it's time to say goodbye

1358
02:13:08,780 --> 02:13:11,780
Like the wind thatlingers
and then goes,

1359
02:13:12,384 --> 02:13:15,384
Just like shadows

1360
02:13:15,887 --> 02:13:18,887
To promises that never came,

1361
02:13:19,424 --> 02:13:22,424
to the love sealed till the end

1362
02:13:24,396 --> 02:13:27,396
To the grass kissing
my weary ankles

1363
02:13:30,836 --> 02:13:33,836
And to the tiny footsteps
following me

1364
02:13:41,847 --> 02:13:44,847
It's time to say goodbye

1365
02:13:46,918 --> 02:13:49,587
Now as darkness falls

1366
02:13:49,588 --> 02:13:52,588
Will a candle be lit again?

1367
02:13:54,793 --> 02:13:57,793
Here I pray...

1368
02:13:58,263 --> 02:14:01,263
nobody shall cry...

1369
02:14:03,969 --> 02:14:06,969
and for you to know...

1370
02:14:08,573 --> 02:14:11,573
how deeply I loved you

1371
02:14:16,348 --> 02:14:19,348
The long wait in the middle
of a hot summer day

1372
02:14:21,653 --> 02:14:24,653
An old path resembling
my father's face

1373
02:14:27,726 --> 02:14:30,726
Even the lonesome wild flower
shyly turning away

1374
02:14:34,366 --> 02:14:37,366
How deeply loved

1375
02:14:39,704 --> 02:14:42,704
How my heart fluttered at
hearing your faint song

1376
02:14:49,681 --> 02:14:52,681
I bless you

1377
02:14:59,958 --> 02:15:02,927
Before crossing the black river

1378
02:15:02,928 --> 02:15:05,928
With my soul's last breath

1379
02:15:09,734 --> 02:15:12,734
I am beginning to dream...

1380
02:15:14,606 --> 02:15:17,606
a bright sunny morning...

1381
02:15:18,376 --> 02:15:21,376
again  I awake,
blinded by the light...

1382
02:15:22,047 --> 02:15:25,047
and meet you...